{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "d4e5f6a7-b8c9-0123-defa-4567890abcde",
    "name": "AGCE KYC Service",
    "description": "KYC verification service for Arab Global Crypto Exchange (Didit-backed).\n\n## Setup\n1. Import this collection AND the AGCE Local environment\n2. **Run Auth → Signup first** so `accessToken` and `userId` are populated\n3. Then **Run KYC → Start Session** — saves `kycSessionId` automatically\n4. Use the webhook requests to simulate Didit status updates (HMAC is signed automatically by a pre-request script)\n\n## Variables (shared with Auth collection)\n- `baseUrlKyc` — KYC service base URL (default `http://localhost:3001`)\n- `accessToken` — set by Auth signup/login\n- `userId` — set by Auth signup/login\n- `kycSessionId` — set by KYC Start Session\n- `diditWebhookSecret` — for HMAC signing (matches kyc_service .env)\n- `jurisdiction` — INDIA / ABU_DHABI / DUBAI / GLOBAL\n\n## Webhook signing\nWebhook requests in this collection have a **pre-request script** that:\n1. Builds the webhook payload using current variables\n2. Canonicalizes it (sorted keys)\n3. Computes HMAC-SHA256 with `diditWebhookSecret`\n4. Sets `X-Signature-V2` and `X-Timestamp` headers\n5. Replaces the body with the canonical signed payload\n\nNo manual signing needed — just hit Send.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check (Gateway)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns ok', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});",
                  "// Note: when accessed via the gateway, this returns the gateway's",
                  "// own health (service: 'agce-gateway'), not the kyc-service's."
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlKyc}}/healthz",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlKyc}}"],
              "path": ["healthz"]
            },
            "description": "Hits the **gateway** health endpoint (not the kyc-service directly). This verifies the gateway is reachable."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "KYC",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Start Session",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Returns session', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('sessionId');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('diditUrl');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "  if (data.sessionId) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('kycSessionId', data.sessionId);",
                  "    console.log('Saved kycSessionId:', data.sessionId);",
                  "  }",
                  "  if (data.diditUrl) {",
                  "    console.log('Open this URL to verify:', data.diditUrl);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlKyc}}/api/v1/kyc/session",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlKyc}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "kyc", "session"]
            },
            "description": "Starts a Didit verification session for the authenticated user. Empty body is fine — the service uses the JWT's `jurisdiction` and the user's contact details automatically.\n\nReturns:\n- `sessionId` — Didit session UUID (saved to env)\n- `diditUrl` — open this in iframe / WebView for verification\n- `status`, `level`, `jurisdiction`\n\nIf an active session already exists, it's returned instead of creating a new one."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Start Session (with details)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const data = pm.response.json().data;",
                  "  if (data.sessionId) pm.environment.set('kycSessionId', data.sessionId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
