    {
      "name": "Webhook (Didit Simulation)",
      "description": "These requests simulate Didit's webhooks. Each one has a pre-request script that signs the payload with HMAC-SHA256-V2 using `diditWebhookSecret`.\n\n**IMPORTANT:** the `kycSessionId` env var must point to a session that exists in the kyc_service Mongo. Either:\n1. Run **Start Session** first (with a valid Didit API key + workflow), OR\n2. Manually seed Mongo with a KYC record using the SESSION_ID from `kycSessionId`",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Webhook: Approved",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Build webhook payload",
                  "const ts = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);",
                  "const body = {",
                  "  session_id: pm.environment.get('kycSessionId') || 'test-session-id',",
                  "  status: 'Approved',",
                  "  webhook_type: 'status.updated',",
                  "  created_at: ts,",
                  "  timestamp: ts,",
                  "  workflow_id: 'wf-postman',",
                  "  vendor_data: pm.environment.get('userId') || 'test-user'",
                  "};",
                  "",
                  "// Canonicalize (sort keys recursively)",
                  "const sortKeys = (obj) => {",
                  "  if (Array.isArray(obj)) return obj.map(sortKeys);",
                  "  if (obj !== null && typeof obj === 'object') {",
                  "    return Object.keys(obj).sort().reduce((acc, k) => {",
                  "      acc[k] = sortKeys(obj[k]);",
                  "      return acc;",
                  "    }, {});",
                  "  }",
                  "  return obj;",
                  "};",
                  "",
                  "const canonical = JSON.stringify(sortKeys(body));",
                  "const secret = pm.environment.get('diditWebhookSecret');",
                  "const signature = CryptoJS.HmacSHA256(canonical, secret).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Hex);",
                  "",
                  "// Inject body + headers",
                  "pm.variables.set('webhookBody', canonical);",
                  "pm.variables.set('webhookSig', signature);",
                  "pm.variables.set('webhookTs', ts.toString());",
                  "",
                  "console.log('Webhook prepared: status=Approved, session_id=' + body.session_id);"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Webhook accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Signature-V2", "value": "{{webhookSig}}" },
              { "key": "X-Timestamp", "value": "{{webhookTs}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{{webhookBody}}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrlKyc}}/api/v1/kyc/webhook",
              "host": ["{{baseUrlKyc}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "kyc", "webhook"]
            },
            "description": "Simulates Didit sending an `Approved` webhook. The pre-request script:\n1. Builds the webhook payload with `status: Approved`\n2. Canonicalizes (sorts keys recursively)\n3. Computes HMAC-SHA256 with `diditWebhookSecret`\n4. Sets `X-Signature-V2` and `X-Timestamp` headers\n\n**Effect:** kyc_service updates the local DB and emits a Kafka event that auth_service consumes to update `User.kycStatus` to APPROVED."
          },
          "response": []
        },
